Went to this place to grab early dinner with my sister. Bar area was quite crowded and my sister was not really comfortable with how crowded it was. We considered leaving but found there was a whole other dining room in the back that was completely empty.    They brought some delicious looking roles fresh from the oven to the table while looking over the menu. Steam still coming off of them and crispy brown perfection outside, we tried the rolls. Unfortunately they were still very doey inside and not completely cooked, so much so that we couldn't really eat them. They have a great menu with lots of fish and things like roast beef dinner, shepherds pie(lamb and beef mix), and chicken pie. I just got a cheeseburger and fries which was good. My sister got the lobster casserole. She said the lobster didn't taste fresh or right and didn't like the peppers in it with the lobster taste together. She ate very little of it and was disappointed, but didn't want to say anything. When the waitress noticed she didn't eat much and asked, she admitted she didn't really like it at all. Without asking the waitress immediately took the meal off the bill and asked if she would like something else, which she didn't. Meals seemed fairly reasonably priced. Burger and fries was $10. Can't remember what lobster was. Market price. We did order a piece of chocolate layer cake for dessert which was served with whipped cream and chocolate sauce. It was good, but was $9 which we thought was quite overpriced for sure. The waitress was wonderful and there was quite a crowd for the time of day, so I might be tempted to go back and try a different dish. I try to remember that some things are harder to get fresh right now with covid and it is the dead of winter, so maybe that's why lobster wasn't fresh. Worth a try if you're in the neighborhood. Large list of beer to choose from and a casual pub atmosphere with lots of booths in bar area and back dining room. Cable TV for watching games and great staff from our experience.

We had their Sunday brunch buffet today and although most of the food was good, they ran out of the 2 main protein dishes - the prime rib and turkey. We told the manager and he didn't even bother to apoligize but did say they were cooking fresh turkey and prime rib in the kitchen.  While waiting we kept picking at the other buffet items, Including a made-to-order omelet.  I was shocked when the cook made it in the same pan as the previous one - without even wiping out the pan!  And, the previous omelet had ham, while mine was vegetarian, not that I'm vegetarian or kosher, but this is definitely not good restaurant cooking practice.  One hour later we were ready to leave, and still no prime rib or turkey.  Oh well we thought, just our luck. BTW, this has also happened a few other times we've eaten there, but usually they've run out of just one of the main dishes.  We had purchased a groupon for a $30 restaurant credit.  We assumed that it would cover the $29.90 bill because the restaurant was running a promotion for $14.95 vs. their regular price of $19.95, but they told us that the promotion did not apply for groupon.  OK, so we reminded them about all the problems again and said we would compomise: they take the groupon and we call it even.  They refused and treated us as if we were in the wrong!  We have been regular customers for at least 25 years.  We will miss 🙁 the wait staff who have been there for most of those years, but don't plan on returning.

Mount Vernon is a great place to go if you want to go out to eat, and want to do it cheaply, but not fast food cheaply.  The food reflects the price and is largely meh, and over the past few times I've gone I've found hair from either the cooking staff or wait staff sitting in my meal.  Their drink selection is better than La Brasa, but that's an incredibly low bar.  Wait staff is incredibly friendly, however, which is largely what gets the restaurant the score I'm giving it now.  The one thing they knock out of the park, though?  If you get a table they serve you yorkshire pudding instead of standard bread rolls.  They really should throw that on the appetizer menu, I'd love to have that as an option when I grab a couple drinks at their bar.
